<p>You probably understand that the point of this exercise is to show how counter-productive it is to sit around, willing the price to move up. Invest and then go do something else.</p>

<p>In this model, you can add another half a million if you spend 3k a month instead of 2k a month. That doesn‚Äôt have to mean pay rise, your disposable income can also grow from the difference between living in a metropolitan area vs moving to a less trendy place. Unless your earnings depend on the virtue shell game of tech startups, it is absolutely doable to cut a lot of costs out just by making decisions that are not fueled by Kool Aid.</p>

